properties.FacilityDescription:
Overview

White Cloud Campground is located in the Tahoe National Forest, near Nevada City and three historic mining towns along Highway 20. The area provides a great escape from urban life.

Natural Features:

The campground is situated in a forest of cedar and Douglas fir trees, at an elevation of 4,200 feet.

Recreation:

The Pioneer Trail stretches 25 miles through the Tahoe National Forest and can be accessed from the campground. The popular path was designated a National Recreation Trail in 2003. Horseback riding, hiking, mountain biking and cross-country skiing are favorite activities on this popular trail.

Facilities:

The campground offers single-family sites, a few of which are designated for tent camping only. Each site is equipped with a picnic table and campfire ring. Flush toilets and drinking water are provided.
properties.FacilityDirections:
From Nevada City, travel east on Highway 20, toward Truckee. Turn right at White Cloud and take the right fork to the campground.

From Interstate 80, take the Highway 20 exit and travel west for 14 miles. Turn left into White Cloud and take the right fork to the campground.
